# Portfolio Website Builder V2 - AI Agent Coding Rules & Harness Guidelines

This guide defines the **core decision-making criteria and hard constraints** that must be followed by any AI agent (Antigravity) modifying code or designing features in this project.

---

## 1. Core Constraints and Architecture Rules

### 1.1. Build-First Static Compilation System
- **No Direct Modification**: Do NOT modify HTML files directly under the `ko/` and `en/` directories. These folders are compiler outputs overwritten on every build execution.
- **Modification Targets**:
  - Markup structure and static layouts: Modify component templates inside [templates/](file:///Users/oasunryo/Files/Antigravity/portfolio_webstie_builer_v2/templates/) (such as `head.html`, `header.html`, `footer.html`, `noise.html`).
  - Data and metadata: Edit list constants inside [projectsData.js](file:///Users/oasunryo/Files/Antigravity/portfolio_webstie_builer_v2/projectsData.js), [newBlogPosts.js](file:///Users/oasunryo/Files/Antigravity/portfolio_webstie_builer_v2/newBlogPosts.js), and [build.js](file:///Users/oasunryo/Files/Antigravity/portfolio_webstie_builer_v2/build.js).
- **Run Compilations**: After modifying code or data, you must run `node build.js` in the project root to refresh the HTML files.

### 1.2. Strict Tech Stack Control
- **No Frameworks**: Do NOT introduce frontend frameworks (e.g., React, Next.js, Vue) or utility-first CSS libraries (e.g., Tailwind CSS).
- **Tech Standards**: Code must be written strictly using **HTML5 + Vanilla CSS + Pure ES6+ JavaScript**.
- **Style Centralization**: All style declarations must reside inside [index.css](file:///Users/oasunryo/Files/Antigravity/portfolio_webstie_builer_v2/index.css) to maintain clean class-based layouts. Minimize inlining CSS properties inside HTML tags.

### 1.3. Localization and Relative Path Resolution
- **Relative Path Swapping**: When compiling multilingual pages, relative paths (`${relPath}`) computed based on the page depth (`depth`) are dynamically referenced. If absolute paths (e.g., `/index.css`, `/logo/favicon.svg`) are hardcoded in templates, add them to the string substitution logic (`compilePage`) in [build.js](file:///Users/oasunryo/Files/Antigravity/portfolio_webstie_builer_v2/build.js) to compile them to relative paths.

---

## 2. Troubleshooting and Browser Quirks

### 2.1. Safari iOS/macOS Layout Fixes
- **Safe Area Header Calculations**: When defining sticky navigation headers (`.sticky-nav`) and top padding (`.pt-24`), incorporate the CSS `env(safe-area-inset-top)` variable to prevent overlaps with mobile notch boundaries:
  ```css
  header.sticky-nav {
    padding-top: calc(1.25rem + env(safe-area-inset-top, 0px));
  }
  ```
- **Modal Overlay Seam Protection**: To prevent gaps when scrolling bounces in Safari, apply negative viewport margins (`top: -10vh; bottom: -10vh; left: -10vw; right: -10vw;`) to the modal overlay (`.side-peek-overlay`).
- **Resetting Scroll Caches**: To avoid bugs where the previous modal's scroll coordinates persist when opening another side peek detail panel, reset the target container scroll top explicitly:
  ```javascript
  body.scrollTop = 0;
  ```

### 2.2. Safari Favicon Cache Bugs
- **Enforce Cache Busting Parameters**: Safari caches broken favicon states indefinitely if loading fails once. Keep the cache-busting query string parameter (`?v=1.0.1`) appended to all link tags, and ensure the root `index.html` also contains the same declarations.

---

## 3. UI Component Conventions

### 3.1. Premium Tooltip System
- **Implementation**: Do NOT use dynamic JS scripts to build tooltips. For accessibility and performance, declare text targets in the `data-tooltip` attribute of HTML elements, and style them using the CSS attribute selector `[data-tooltip]`:
  ```html
  <a href="..." data-tooltip="Tooltip Text">Link</a>
  ```

### 3.2. Carousels and Scroll Sliders
- **Dynamic Step Calculations**: To prevent coordinate misalignment inside `.carousel-container` during screen resizing, compute movement intervals dynamically by evaluating both `offsetWidth` and card `gap` variables.

### 3.3. Blog and Project Content Markup Rules
- **Direct HTML Insertion**: Detailed body content (`content`, `prose`) for posts and projects is rendered as raw HTML in the browser without markdown processing.
- **No Markdown Bold Syntax**: Writing markdown bold tags like `**text**` in body data will display raw asterisks (`**`) in the viewport.
- **Standard Emphasizing**: Use the HTML standard `<strong>text</strong>` tag to preserve markup formatting.

### 3.4. Optical Icon Alignment
- **Vertical Offsets**: Small SVG icons (e.g. 12–14px) placed adjacent to text can appear visually elevated even with `align-items: center` declared on the container.
- **Solution**: Adjust visual alignment by assigning relative positioning offsets such as `position: relative; top: 1px;` (or between 0.5px to 1.5px) to the SVG elements.

### 3.5. Interactive Preview Card Positioning
- **Dynamic Coordinates Correction**: Tooltips or preview cards tracked by mouse movements are prone to layout lag, rendering their height (`offsetHeight`) as 0 or drawing them offscreen.
- **Solution**:
  1. Register a `ResizeObserver` to re-evaluate card coordinates whenever content changes or image assets load.
  2. If the boundary calculations show the card card bottom exceeds the viewport height, position the card above the cursor or clamp it (`window.innerHeight - previewHeight - 15`) to keep it visible.
  3. Hook into the initial mouse coordinates immediately on `mouseenter` to render the card smoothly on the first frame.

### 3.6. No Decorative Emojis or Icons
- **Strict Emoji Limitations**: Do NOT use decorative emojis (e.g. 📊, 🔬, 💡, 🚀) or miscellaneous icons in headings, subtitles, or layout boxes.
- **Design Philosophy**: Keep content layouts minimal and standard, relying strictly on clean typography to establish a professional tone of voice.

### 3.7. Redundancy Elimination in Lists
- **No Text Duplication**: When implementing hover previews for list-view pages (e.g., blog list), do not duplicate list item texts inside the hover preview card.
- **Implementation Standard**: The main list layouts should only display high-density structured metadata columns (Category, Date, etc.) alongside the title. Keep detailed summaries (`Description`) hidden in the main body, storing them inside a `data-description` attribute to be exposed only on hover card previews.
- **Layout Stabilization (Fixed Width Columns)**: To avoid text overlapping during viewport shrinking, specify grid dimensions as: `1fr [fixed-width category] [fixed-width date] [fixed-width read-time]` (e.g., `1fr 120px 100px 80px`).
- **Alignment Conventions**: Center-align category badges, dates, and read times on desktop (`text-align: center`), and restore them to left-aligned (`text-align: left`) on mobile layouts using media queries.
- **Category Badge Color Themes**: Use defined pastel background colors for category chips (Architecture: `#edede9`, Career: `#d6ccc2`, Hardware: `#f5ebe0`, Insight: `#e3d5ca`, Semiconductor: `#d5bdaf`), and enforce `#1a1a1a` text color to guarantee readability.

### 3.8. Grid/List View Toggle and Caching
- **View Caching**: Persist the user's grid/list toggle selections across page reloads using browser `localStorage` (key: `projects-view`).
- **Grid Mode and Line Clamping**: When grid mode is active, render items in a 2-column layout (`grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr)`). To maintain uniform card heights, clamp description summaries to a maximum of 2 lines (`line-clamp: 2`).
- **Skip Floating Previews in Grid Mode**: Because grid cards display sufficient visual and text content, bypass floating hover cards in grid mode via early returns to reduce visual clutter.

---

## 4. Media Assets and Performance Optimization

### 4.1. GitHub + jsDelivr CDN Asset Hosting
- **Keep Repositories Light**: Do NOT commit heavy image or chart assets to the web builder code repository.
- **Standard Asset Repository**: Upload media assets to the public repository `oasunryo/portfolio-assets`.
- **CDN Integration**: Reference assets using absolute `jsDelivr` URLs inside blog post data files (`newBlogPosts.js`):
  ```text
  https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/oasunryo/portfolio-assets@main/[path/filename]
  ```

### 4.2. Directory & Naming Conventions for Assets
- **Asset Directories**: Isolate media assets inside designated folders matching their post or project slugs:
  - Blog: `blog/[yyyy-mm-dd-slug]/` (e.g., `blog/2026-05-08-amkor-osat-interview-prep/`)
  - Project: `projects/[project-slug]/` (e.g., `projects/capillary-bonding/`)
- **Naming Standards**: Prevent broken link errors by using only **lowercase kebab-case** names without spaces or Korean characters (e.g., `wafer-process-chart.webp`).

### 4.3. Format and Lossless Compression
- **Lazy Loading**: Enforce `loading="lazy"` on all `<img>` tags inside body sections, and declare aspect ratios (`width`, `height`) to prevent Cumulative Layout Shifts (CLS).
- **Format Choices**: Use **WebP** for bitmap images (photos, charts) and **SVG** for vector structures (diagrams, simple designs).
- **Automated Compression**: The GitHub Action workflow (`image-actions`) configured in the asset repository compresses images losslessly on push, ensuring file sizes remain optimized.
